<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2575] CXFRS Routing in 2.2.0 does not behave like in 2.0.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2575</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CXFRS Routing in Camel 2.0.0 works  well with these endPoints:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;cxf:rsServer id=&quot;restRouter&quot; address=&quot;/restRouter/&quot;	&lt;br/&gt;
      serviceClass=&quot;com.project.service.impl.ServiceManagerImpl&quot;   /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;     &amp;lt;cxf:rsClient id=&quot;restEndpoint&quot; address=&quot;http://localhost:8080/services/rest&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
      serviceClass=&quot;com.project.service.impl.ServiceManagerImpl&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Camel 2.2.0, Routing fails with error causing the CXF Client to invoke a 404 not found Rest Service which is &apos;http://localhost:8080/services/rest/restRouter/Path&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The address of cxf:rsClient is being appended by the cxf:rsServer&apos;s address&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Spring&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
